OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: John
OL,4,CHaddock
OL,6,FThe deployment to the South coast
OL,7,Ffollowed several attacks in the
OL,8,FChannel by German E-boats which were
OL,9,Ffast and heavily armed motor torpedo
OL,10,Fboats.
OL,12,F"They were causing a lot of damage and
OL,13,Fnuisance to the Allied forces that
OL,14,Fwere preparing to go across on D-Day,"
OL,15,Fhe said.
OL,17,F"There were many furrowed brows and
OL,18,Fone particular disaster and a lot of
OL,19,Fcasualties - kept quiet for the reason
OL,20,Fof security and morale.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
