OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: John
OL,4,CHaddock
OL,6,F"One American general was so concerned
OL,7,Fthinking what would happen on D-Day if
OL,8,Fthere was a mass attack by these E-
OL,9,Fboats.
OL,11,F"Our instructions were basically to
OL,12,Fpatrol the English Channel and seek
OL,13,Fand destroy E-boats. Which is what we
OL,14,Fattempted to do. For this purpose we
OL,15,Fwere equipped with bombs which we
OL,16,Fdidn't normally carry but it was
OL,17,Fthought for this type of operation
OL,18,Fbombs would be more effective.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
