OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: John
OL,4,CHaddock
OL,6,F"The patrols were mainly done at
OL,7,Fnight. A single aircraft would fly
OL,8,Falong the Channel and it would be
OL,9,Ftracked by radar from the South coast
OL,10,Fand that radar would also search the
OL,11,FChannel for enemy E-boats and if it
OL,12,Ffound one or two it would work out the
OL,13,Fdirection for us to fly to get there.
OL,15,F"They also told us when we reached the
OL,16,Ftarget which we couldn't always tell
OL,17,Fbecause it's pitch-black down on the
OL,18,Fwater.
OL,20,F"Then we would drop bombs."
